Looks like the aarch64-gnu, self-hosted, ARM64, linux runner doesn't start at all or starts much later than the others:

  • https://github.com/rust-lang-ci/rust/runs/1829920671 - "Started 2 minutes ago" while all other runners started about two hours ago.
  • https://github.com/rust-lang-ci/rust/runs/1827119046 - didn't start at all, but now says "Cancelled 2 minutes ago" while all other runners started 12 hours ago and the whole thing was already timed out

Not sure what happened there.
Yeah, I saw this too, not sure what's going on
I restarted it, stuff should start running again
